I"<p>In Windows, to make a python script “double-clickable”, need to use a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">batch</code> file, which has extension <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.bat</code>.  Using <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">conda</code> distribution for Python, need to do:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>CALL conda.bat activate base
python python_script.py
</code></pre></div></div>
:ET